    <string name="step0_description">Get a large bowl and sift the flour, sugar, baking power, and salt.</string>
    <string name="step1_description">Get another bowl, and separate the egg whites into it.</string>
    <string name="step2_description">Beat the egg whites until stiff peaks form.</string>
    <string name="step3_description">In a third bowl, mix together the egg yolks, milk, oil, and vanilla. Stir slightly.</string>
    <string name="step4_description">Add the egg/milk/oil mix to the bowl with the dry ingredients, and mix well.</string>
    <string name="step5_description">Fold the egg whites into the mixture</string>
    <string name="step6_description">With a kitchen towel, spread some oil over the waffle maker to avoid sticking.</string>
    <string name="step7_description">Pour the batter evenly onto the waffle iron, close it, and let it cook for 5 to 10 minutes.</string>
    <string name="step8_description">You can store batter in the fridge for up to three days, or freeze it for later.</string>
